        "client_msg_id": "9cf3de22-0039-4133-835f-7d67f092eca6",
        "text": "It is a bit tricky, since the crowd is only one aspect of home advantage. Others, including less travel and familiarity with varying pitch dimensions and conditions still apply. So I've been trying to adjust crowd size alone. The <http:\/\/football-data.co.uk|football-data.co.uk> dataset has crowd sizes for some leagues, and where it doesn't, stadium capacity is a pretty good proxy (with the advantage of being available before the match and therefore a viable predictor). These can then simply be set to zero for matches without crowds. This seems broadly to work though I'd like more matches in my dataset to validate this (on the other hand I'd like to see crowds back).",
